    marketBackground: "",
    detailedAnalysis: "The social media ban proposals come amid growing concerns over the impact of social media on young people's mental health and wellbeing. In Australia, the proposed ban would prohibit children under the age of 16 from using social media platforms, while in the UK, a similar ban is being considered as part of a broader effort to regulate online content. Dr. Emma Taylor, a leading expert on child psychology, notes that 'social media can have a profound impact on young people's self-esteem and mental health, and it's essential that we take steps to protect them.' However, others argue that such bans would be an overreach of government authority and could have unintended consequences, such as driving young people to use alternative, unregulated platforms.\n\n---\n\nAuthor: Shiva Sandeep\n\nTelegram: @its_terabyte\n\nWhatsApp:\n\n*Default WhatsApp profile image placeholder*\n\nPublished by PulseTrends\n\n---",
