    executiveSummary: "The Indian IPO market has seen a surge in activity from small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), with over 20 filings in the last quarter. Recent subscription data indicates strong investor appetite for SMEs, driven by attractive valuations and growth potential. As the market continues to evolve, it\'s likely that we\'ll see even more SMEs tapping the capital markets to raise funds.",
